  <!-- ============ UPGRADE (herbal drinks add-on, not a plan upsell — they suit a low-carb month) ============ -->
  <section class="upgrade">
    <div class="upgrade-inner reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">Want the Full Tradition?</p>
      <h2>Add the 30-day herbal drinks</h2>
      <p>Food is one pillar of Zuo Yue Zi; the herbal drinks are another. Fifteen formulas, stage by stage, one cup a day — no sugar, no carbs, and nothing that works against the way you're eating this month.</p>
      <a href={orderUrl('local_lowcarb', 'en')} class="btn btn-primary">Add the herbal drinks — {usd(products.herbal_drink.price * 30)}</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ FAQ ============ -->
  <section class="faq-band" id="faq">
    <svg class="botan faq-botan" viewBox="0 0 200 200" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
      <g>
        <path d="M185 25 C165 60 140 88 112 108" stroke="#5E6B4F" stroke-width="1.8" fill="none" opacity="0.55"/>
        <ellipse cx="150" cy="62" rx="10" ry="16" fill="#5E6B4F" opacity="0.35" transform="rotate(30 150 62)"/>
        <ellipse cx="98" cy="118" rx="28" ry="34" fill="#D99FB0" opacity="0.5"/>
        <path d="M98 86 C111 94 117 108 113 122 C109 134 100 142 98 144 C96 142 87 134 83 122 C79 108 85 94 98 86Z" fill="#C77D7D" opacity="0.45"/>
        <circle cx="98" cy="118" r="9" fill="#E8C46A" opacity="0.75"/>
      </g>
    </svg>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head reveal">
        <p class="eyebrow">Good Questions</p>
        <h2>Before you decide</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list reveal">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What exactly is left out?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Rice and grains at lunch and dinner, the breakfast porridge, the two daily desserts, and the sweet daily healing drink. That's it.</p><p>Everything else stays: the breakfast egg dish, the lunch soup, the Taiwanese postpartum soup and dinner soup, entrées, and warm vegetables at both meals — all cooked from scratch and delivered fresh daily. The <a href="//file.jingmommy.com/f/Meal_Comparison_Chart.pdf">Meal Comparison Chart</a> shows every plan side by side.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Without the rice, is it still enough food?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Fair question — and yes, on paper it's our leanest plan: no rice, no porridge, no dessert. But fewer items doesn't mean less filling. Protein and slow-simmered soups sit with you longer than a bowl of rice does, so most moms find a day of Low Carb keeps them satisfied between meals. You still get three warm meals a day, with an entrée and vegetables at both lunch and dinner.</p><p>If you'd like to see for yourself before committing, the <a href="//file.jingmommy.com/f/Menu.pdf">Full Menu</a> lists every dish, and a single day is {usd(products.local_lowcarb_1d.price)}.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Is this a weight-loss plan?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>No. This is a Zuo Yue Zi recovery plan, and it exists to nourish you — not to make you smaller. We don't make weight or body promises, and we'd be wary of anyone who did during your first month postpartum.</p><p>Mothers usually choose this plan because they're managing blood sugar, because larger amounts of carbs don't sit well with them, or because low-carb is already how they eat. If you have a medical reason for eating this way, please loop in your own doctor — and we're glad to share the full menu with them.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Can I add the herbal drinks?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes — they're an optional add-on at <strong>{usd(products.herbal_drink.price * 30)} for the 30 days</strong>, one cup a day. Fifteen formulas that follow the traditional recovery sequence, stage by stage. They contain no sugar, so they sit comfortably alongside a low-carb month.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How does delivery work, and when should I order?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>In our regular service area, meals are delivered fresh every day and we aim to reach your door before noon — actual times shift with traffic and routes, so an exact hour isn't guaranteed. Remote areas receive every-other-day delivery, and an additional delivery fee may apply. Refrigerate your meals on arrival, and heat them thoroughly before eating.</p><p>Order at least a month before your due date if you can. The week your baby arrives, you won't have the bandwidth to compare plans or fill out forms — and you shouldn't have to. Your start date can be adjusted once the baby comes.</p></div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

